        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of thunderstorms
with heavy rain over Buckingham, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Poor drainage flooding and ponding of water on roads.

Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Dillwyn...
New Canton...
Toga...
Centenary...
Sheppards...
and Andersonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter and avoiding poor
drainage areas.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
